          <p>We recommend that you use a private taxi to reach the hotel from the airport. Look for Traslado Exclusivo on the main hall of the airport.</p>
        </section>
        <section class="col-md-4">
          <i class="fa fa-map-marker"></i>
          <h2>Explore</h2>
          <p>Rosario is the third largest city in Argentina, tucked into a bend of the Paraná River 300 km northwest of Buenos Aires. Begin your day with a walk on the riverbank and a coffee at <a href="http://www.puertoespana.com.ar/online/riomio/">Río Mío</a>. Visit the <a href="http://www.monumentoalabandera.gob.ar/">national flag memorial</a> and take the elevator up for a great view of the city. Have a delicious steak at <a href="http://www.puertoespana.com.ar/online/donferro/">Don Ferro</a>, built on an old railway station, or <a href="http://www.parrillalaestancia.com.ar/">Parrilla La Estancia</a>, frequented by Lionel Messi. Bike or jog in <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Parque_de_España">Parque de España</a>, or stock up on leather goods in <a href="http://www.alto-rosario.com.ar/">Alto Rosario</a>. When the sun sets, take a stroll down <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oroño_Boulevard">Boulevard Oroño</a>, a two-way street bustling with restaurants, upscale buildings and traditional houses. To cap your night, stop by <a href="http://www.rockandfellers.com.ar/">Rock &amp; Feller's</a> to enjoy great food, drinks, and atmosphere.</p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
